  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-10-12T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Power Outage for Weather Emergency Repair Act or the POWER Act \n\nThis bill directs the Department of Energy (DOE)to maintain a database of information on electricity outages that is publicly accessible and includes the specific cause and impact of the outages.\n\nDOE shall promulgate a rule to require each electric utility to report to the Energy Information Administration information on electricity outages that interrupt service resulting in a loss of more than 300 megawatts or affecting at least 50,000 electric customers."
  }, 
